<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="126" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">War Department, Adjutant General’s
                                Office, Cables Section Files</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Adjutant General</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McCain</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Military Representative on the Supreme War Council</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_BGTH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-29">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>39. For Secretary <persName corresp="#p_BND1">Baker</persName>:</p>
                            <p>Reference cablegram 67 signed <persName corresp="#p_BGTH1">Bliss</persName>, the action of the President is as
                                follows:</p>
                            <p>The President concurs in the joint note of the permanent military
                                representatives of the Supreme War Council in the sense formulated
                                in your No. 67, March 28, and wishes you to regard yourself
                                authorized to decide questions of immediate cooperation or
                                replacement. March.<note n="1" xml:id="d126fn1">Maj. Gen.
                                        <persName>Peyton C. March</persName>, Acting Chief of
                                    Staff.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McCain</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>